POLICE in Limpopo have arrested 11 members of the community at Zaaiplaas, outside Groblersdal.The residents were bust on Saturday for torching the house of Lolo Madonsela&rsquo;s parents, after the man allegedly killed his neighbour and sucked her blood.The community members, aged between 17 and 52, were bust for arson and public violence.The 30-year-old murder suspect was allegedly found by a passerby busy chopping up 39-year-old Anna Mashifane&rsquo;s body with a sharp axe on Tuesday. He was later arrested at the scene.He was denied bail after appearing briefly before the Groblersdal Magistrates Court on Thursday and is expected to appear again tomorrow for a formal bail application.Chaos erupted following his arrest and angry community members forced his family to leave the village. Moatshe Ngoepe, Limpopo police spokesman, said: &ldquo;It is alleged that the local community members mobilised and burnt the suspect&rsquo;s parents house worth an estimated R250 000. &ldquo;All the eleven suspects are facing arson and public violence charges,&rdquo; said Ngoepe.They were arrested by the special joint operation composed of various police units. &ldquo;They are expected to appear before the Groblersdal Magistrates Court today.&rdquo; Ngoepe said more arrests are still expected as investigations continue. He warned community members against doing anything that can get them into trouble. &ldquo;Members of the community are once more warned to refrain from taking the law into their hands because that is a serious offence punishable by law.&rdquo;